Arsene Wenger: Arsenal manager calls press 'boring' after spat
Media playback is not supported on this deviceArsenal manager Arsene Wenger calls the press "boring" after getting involved in a spat with a journalist about team selection.The Frenchman was criticised for not playing goalkeeper Petr Cech - a summer signing - in Tuesday'sChampions League defeat by Olympiakosat Emirates Stadium, after a mistake by his replacement David Ospina cost a goal.Wenger says the media "lack a bit of creativity", accusing the press of "following a bandwagon that is very, very boring".